cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with learning bilingual word representations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a probabilistic model for learning these representations. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves natural language processing and cross-lingual classification. The use of distributed representations suggests it could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of a cross-lingual classification task suggests it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
